{
  "stem": "12768.3",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Bones and skin was all-- and we were warned, do not give them anything, only if they want a cigarette.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "It was all we could give these-- they. they told us, do not give them food.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because they have to go through a whole regiment of, of food over the next year.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And I have seen dead people, I mean, afterwards who are lying by the border and, and Germany.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But this here was the worst of the worst that you really see, the piles of bones lying, the stiff bodies just lying around.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "This was just stiff bodies that were still alive.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And I remember specifically giving a Frenchman a cigarette.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And the only thing I got was just the eyes, a blink with the eyes.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "That was thank you, I presume.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "But so my mother had come to Sweden.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And I didn't see my mother, of course, until-- and I was sent home from the military, which was toward the end of July of 1945.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And we were sent home, and-- because we had give our uniform.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "So we had some old clothes on.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "And they had stored our clothes.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "So finally, I could change into regular street clothes.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And then my mom and dad had been out walking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And I was standing outside our home in [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And I saw my mother and my father come walking.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And, of course, I must say that my mother and father have never really been-- because they had never learned to be excited, you know, in, in such a way, you know, that you show emotion or you show love.",
      "word_count": 40
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "But I knew it was there.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "I went and hugged my mother, and, of course, shook hands with my father.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "Because that was what men did.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
